<exploration xml:id="warm-converNum-multipliquemosNumDel11Al19" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>30: I counted by 10. I just knew it.</li>
      <li>39: <m>3\times10=30</m>. I just added 3 more groups of 3 which is 9 to make 39.</li>
      <li>78: Once I knew <m>3\times13=39</m>, then I doubled 39 to get <m>6\times13</m>, which is 78.</li>
      <li>78: <m>3\times20=60</m>, <m>3\times6=18</m>, <m>60+18=78</m>.</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


